<br>
Saw a Necro today with Dire Charm, belive me, it aint very funny to summon your pet afterwards. It is sick to see those quading 130 pets, they ripp apart exp mobs in seconds. That necro easy soloed 4 mobs in the same time I soloed 1, and I was using epic and Boots of Bladecalling I also had regen and kodiaks so Mana wasn't a problem.<br>
<br>
I don't really expect to get a pet that strong, because frankly I think Verant will nerf Dire Charm in some way, I doubt it was meant to be possible for Necros, Enchanters and druids to gain 1 yellow bubble in less than 30mins. But it feel stupid that the prime pet class now are dropped down to 4th pet class.<br>
<br>
Then add to the fact that some of our spell are broken since Kunark, some of our skills don't work ... Even the fact epicpet look like a human and bolts not showing anymore.<br>
<br>
Then they did the major melee upgrade a few months ago they said this wasn't the caster upgrades, but they should look at those as soon as Luclin was released. What happend with this, Luclin been out a while now how long shall we wait? Or have Verant decided that Luclin was the fix they was talking about?<br>
<br>
We really need to get a straight answer about that. Since Ronaldor seems to be on a good side with Alan maybe he can get a straight answer on that question.<br>
<br>
Is the caster improvments that was mention a few months ago considered done?<br>
If they not considered done, then can we expect them to happen? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rhasinfirestorm>Rhasin Firestorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 150<br> <font color=#333333>(1/11/02 6:13:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=40.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Petition about improved skills and bugfix</span><hr size=1> Edit: Err... After reading my reply to this and the post before it.. I'm wondering how in heck I managed to post to the wrong topic on that :P Sheesh. Sorry guys if my reply seemed a little out there :P <p>Rhasin Firestorm<BR>
