<br>
Mages are so far behind on the power curve right now... or the usefullness curve... or the raid contributions curve... hell, ANY curve there is we're bottom of it, it seems.<br>
<br>
Enchanters, Necros, &amp; Druids can now get effectively a yellow of XP every 30 minutes (I have verified this with a 60 Druid friend of mine, as well as a 60 Chanter. They both can get those rates).  Because of special skills and how they boost the melee classes now, there are monks soloing away with 4 to 6 times as many AA points as ANY caster I know (this may change with Dire Charm, tho). I personally know melee-types who've got over 100+ AA Points. That just nauseates me a tad when I'm still struggling to get out of level 55... and a few of the things that Verant PROMISED US as regular fixes (i.e. /pet hold) got made into Alternate Advancement items.<br>
<br>
Overall, I am both rousingly pleased and excruciatingly pissed off at Shadows of Luclin, as an expansion. <p><center><image src="http://home.houston.rr.com/jtully1/tunisig.jpg"><br><b>Tuni Gearspinner</b><br>
