<br>
It seems to me that Magicians largely suffer from one of the same problems that Druids have, that is being middle ground across the board and not being able to excel in any one area. Yes, we  can do alot of damage absorbtion, and alot of damage dealing, however we can't compare with the classes which excel at either. Combine this with an increase of high personel requirement zones which will almost ensure that you'll have several damage absorbers and damage dealers along, and a severe lack of utility (disabled CoH anyone?), and you have a class which, on paper, looks pretty good, but in practice, is suffering.<br>
<br>
Until we get a long time magician at a high enough level in Verant in order to effect some serious changes, I doubt these problems will ever go away either. <p><IMG SRC="http://www.rpi.edu/~redina/sig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unoonievioletskies.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NoonieVioletskies</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 144<br> <font color=#333333>(1/12/02 4:31:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=40.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Petition about improved skills and bugfix</span><hr size=1> look, guys... you are compairing a class w/ a very potent arch ability aaxp skill, to a class without an arch ability aaxp skill.<br>
<br>
what im trying to say is, before knocking dire charm as unfair at least compair a frenzied burnout pet to a dire charmed pet. frenzy burnout CAN be refreshed, and it gives our pet +200 atk (!) and +90 haste, amongst other + stats.<br>
<br>
if the dire charm pet <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  still</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> outdamages the frenzy burnout pet, then i fullly agree, either nerf d.c. or upgrad f.b.<br>
<br>
also, you have to take into consideration that dire charm is limited to mobs under 46. frenzied burnout however can be used anywhere, without any limitations. paired with pet hold, this skill will make us much more raid friendly.<br>
<br>
<br>
one more thing:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> It is sick to see those quading 130 pets, they ripp apart exp mobs in seconds. That necro easy soloed 4 mobs in the same time I soloed 1, and I was using epic and Boots of Bladecalling I also had regen and kodiaks so Mana wasn't a problem.<br>
