anyway, in the very near future i see verant nerfing d.c. so that you cannot heal or buff your perma-charmed pet. <br>
verant quite simply <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  did not</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> intend on people using these perma charmed npcs as permanent super pets (as strange as that sounds). <br>
charm is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  primarily</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> a cc spell, and only secondary an offensive spell. <br>
its the kinda thing which was intended to be used like loh -- just in case in a messy situation (for example, in an undead dungeon where the chanter died due to a bad pull, the necro in your group could hit dire charm and potentially save the group.) <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=33330" target="new"><b>Noonie Violetskies</b>, 55 High Elven Conjurer</a> <br><b>Aylliah Ravenlure</b>, 32 Erudite Enchantress<br> Morell Thule server.</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unoonievioletskies.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NoonieVioletskies</A> at: 1/12/02 4:39:33 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=zeem>Zeem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#333333>(1/12/02 5:17:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=40.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Class skills</span><hr size=1> Noonie,<br>
<br>
Frenzy Burnout can't be refreshed, it is 72min refresh cycle on it, and the buff last 36sec, after the 36sec are up your pet suicide.<br>
Someone posted a log with a frenzid pet, it kinda looks like the pet even miss more than usually. It say it Flurry and Rampage, rampage might be hard to see if no other mobs near, the Flurry didn't even show (there should been 2 extra hits). <br>
It can't compare to Dire charm.<br>
Luclin have ALOT of way undercon mobs, go into Griegs end and you will find green mobs that hit for 150+ (and rampage), I heard someone said the mobs near entrance of Deep was Dire charmable, and those hit for more than 200. <br>
Go into Acrylia near ring of fire and those skellies hit for over 130, at round three of ring of fire the skellies that spawns are green but still hit for 160. I could go on, but a chanter will in 90% of the exp zones have no problem at all finding mobs that hit for 125-135.<br>
<br>
The problem aint either that they just gave Enchanters the skill, they also gave necromancers and druids, so that suddenly three classes that now have very good pets that clearly outdmg us.<br>
If Frenzy was permanent buff or even 36 min buff and it added 20pt dmg , 200 attack 95% haste, flurry rampage it would be good, it kinda would have been half as good as Direcharm, but a 36sec buff there you lose your pet and you can't really see the diffrence are useless.<br>
<br>
The truth is that I really wanted to see ONE good class skill that was worth it, just ONE. Pet hold is the only one I will take as it is now. <br>
From what I seen there someclass skills that have extremly powerfull skills, then you see a Pally do a 5k critical hit you feel kinda weak.<br>
<br>
For start they could do a few things that would make me feel alittle better. <br>
Lower the refresh timer of Elemantal forms and remove the kos component (hello the skill cost a fortune and gives less improvment than wizard familiars).<br>
Increase the duration of Frenzy burnout to permanent, and make sure it add some extra dmg.<br>
Give us Spell casting fury mastery, I could have agreed that this should only been a wizardskill, but then Druids get it mages certanly should too.<br>
And finaly give us some equal to Dire Charm, well maybe they should call it something else since we never charmed stuff before ...  Maybe call it Monstersumming mastery .. or something, instead of charm a mob and instead of do like normal monstersummoning (summon an elemantal and put monster skin on it), instead it cloned any L40-L45 mob that happend to be in the zone and made it your pet. Same refresh timer as Dire charm ofcourse, a little lower risk than Direcharm, but yuo couldn't be sure you got a L40 crappet or a L45 good pet. This would fit our profile, it would be easy to do, and it wouldn't be more powerfull than Direcharm.<br>
<br>
As it is now, none of our class skills are good, they really need to balance these stuff out a bit. We where the weakest class before Luclin, Luclin but us even further behind (ok, maybe bard was worse).<br>
<br>
But as I said before the most important thing I want to know is this.<br>
<br>
Is the caster improvments that was mention a few months ago considered done?<br>
If they not considered done, then can we expect them to happen?  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rhasinfirestorm>Rhasin Firestorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 155<br> <font color=#333333>(1/12/02 6:13:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=40.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Class skills</span><hr size=1> Frankly, for something alongs the Monstersummoning Mastery, I'd love to see it be something passive and go off our Monster Summoning spells. Cast MS2 or MS3 (ratings change, as does what you can summon), but you get an almost identical copy of that monster that you randomly summon. Of course, it would tend to work better in higher powered zones and less in newbie zones, but hey, I'd go for that.<br>
<br>
But basically, Dire Charm is overpowering. ESPECIALLY if one can cast beneficial buffs on the charmie, heal it, etc. Isn't this going to be Kael all over again? <p>Rhasin Firestorm<BR>
